= SDLMod =
An enumeration of key modifier masks.


== Values ==
{|
|KMOD_NONE
|0
|-
|KMOD_LSHIFT
|the left Shift key
|-
|KMOD_RSHIFT
|the right Shift key
|-
|KMOD_LCTRL
|the left Ctrl (Control) key
|-
|KMOD_RCTRL
|the right Ctrl (Control) key
|-
|KMOD_LALT
|the left Alt key
|-
|KMOD_RALT
|the right Alt key
|-
|KMOD_LGUI
|the left GUI key (often the Windows key)
|-
|KMOD_RGUI
|the right GUI key (often the Windows key)
|-
|KMOD_NUM
|the Num Lock key (may be located on an extended keypad)
|-
|KMOD_CAPS
|the Caps Lock key
|-
|KMOD_MODE
|the !AltGr key
|-
|<style="color: #808080;">KMOD_RESERVED
|<style="color: #808080;">reserved for future use
|}

